      "content": "It is completely understandable why you feel this way when the scale of the crisis feels so absolute, and your frustration with the \"band-aid\" mentality is valid. However, the idea that we are just \"rearranging deck chairs\" ignores the fact that the ship is still floating, and even a sinking vessel can be made safer for those on board. Many people find meaning not by ignoring the collapse, but by actively working to make the remaining time together more humane, equitable, and conscious.",
